Setup
-------------

To setup,
run 

	source setup.sh

from the current directory.

To complete the setup run 

./build_ajit_lib.sh 

inside the AJIT toolchain docker,  
from the driver/ directory.

Contents
-----------

driver/
	a set of routines to control and monitor
	the accelerator engine.


examples/
	dma_check/
		Basic DMA test with polling
		(uses only dma controller, not threads)

	big_dma/
		DMA of 8KB of data 
		(uses only dma controller, not threads)
	
	dotp_big_i8/
		i8 dot product on 32KB chunk of data.
		Polling based, uses 4 threads.

	mmul_i32_opt/
		Matrix multiply, with use of "symbolic"
		APARA mcode and the use of dot-product
		as a macro.  Threads are managed by 
		polling.

	mmul_i32_opt_with_interrupts
		Matrix i32 128x128 multiply, with the use of "symbolic"
		APARA mcode and the use of dot-product
		as a macro.   Threads are managed via
		interrupts.

	mmul_i8_opt_with_interrupts
		Matrix i8 256x256  multiply, with the use of "symbolic"
		APARA mcode and the use of dot-product
		as a macro.   Threads are managed via
		interrupts.

memory_layout/

	Total 36 bit address space is divided
	into different sections.

refs/
	APARA document.
tex/

pdf/
	presentation about the programming model
	etc..

utils/
	Utilities to convert APARA object code
	into blobs in AJIT assembly code. The
	resulting AJIT assembly code is linked 
	with the AJIT application to produce
	the final AJIT executable (mmap file).
